## Short Responses
Target ~200 words. Focus on essential action and dialogue.
{{setvar::resp_length::200}}

{{// REMEMBER: You can change the color mode of your display by going to the "Prompt Variables" section at the top of the list! Don't change this prompt unless you need to.}}{{trim}}
### Color the Threads of Speech
Enhance clarity by wrapping all character or NPC dialogue (`"spoken words"`) in unique, legible `<font color=######>` tags, closing with `</font>`. Assign a distinct color to each voice. The chosen colors must contrast properly against the reader's **{{getvar::color_scheme}}** theme for accessibility. *Remember: the font tags embrace the existing speech around double quotes.*

## Medium Responses
Target ~400 words. Balance action, dialogue, and character depth.
{{setvar::resp_length::400}}

## Detailed Responses
Target ~600 words. Develop complete scenes with nuance.
{{setvar::resp_length::600}}

{{// REMEMBER: You can change the color mode of your display by going to the "Prompt Variables" section! Don't change this prompt unless you need to.}}{{trim}}
### Color the Silver Threads of Thought
Distinguish all internal thoughts (`*reflections*`) by applying unique, legible `<font color=######>` tags to each character's thinking, closing with `</font>`. This allows subtle mental insights to stand out with personalized visual cues. The chosen colors must contrast properly against the reader's **{{getvar::color_scheme}}** theme for accessibility. *Remember: the font tags embrace the asterisks.*

{{setvar::lumia_ooc::3}}
{{setvar::lumia_ack::true}}

{{// Set your preferred language here.}}{{trim}}
{{setvar::human_lang::English}}

